        <Parent_String>concrete by property [300010776], concrete [300010737], inorganic material [300010360], materials by composition [300212963], materials (substances) [300010358], Materials (hierarchy name) [300010357], Materials Facet [300264091]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Concrete having the characteristic of being resistant to the formation of sulfates due to limiting values of sulfate-ion content in water, the use of grade the use of sulfate resistance portland cement which is low in tricalcium aluminate, or other factors; desirable because this quality protects structural elements from attack by dissolved sulfates in surrounding water or soil.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052195/Miller, Sulfate Resistant Cement (1952)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>能抵抗硫酸鹽生成的混凝土；此特性可能源於水中硫酸根離子含量的限定值，或者所用之波特蘭水泥等級(因其三鈣鋁酸鹽含量低而具備抗硫酸鹽特性)所引起，但也可能緣於其他原因；此種混凝土因能保護結構元件不受周邊水中或土中所溶出的硫酸鹽侵蝕而受到喜愛。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
